\(x_t\)\(x_{t+1}\)f

f <- function(x, r){ r * x * (1 - x) }

x0 <- 0.9
r <- 3.5

100 step

t_max <- 100

for

f_simulation <- function(x0, r, t_max){
  x_all <- NULL
  x <- x0
  for(t in 1:t_max){
    x <- f(x, r)
    x_all <- c(x_all, x)
  }
  
  return(x_all)
}

tibble

f_arrange <- function(x_all){
  t_max <- length(x_all)
  
  dat <-
    tibble(
      t = 2:(t_max+1),
      x_pre = x_all
    ) %>% 
    bind_rows(tibble(t = 1, x_pre = x0)) %>% 
    arrange(t) %>% 
    mutate(x_post = lead(x_pre)) %>% 
    filter(!is.na(x_post))
  
  return(dat)
}

dat <-
  f_simulation(x0, r, t_max) %>% 
  f_arrange()

dat %>% head(5)

gg_line <- function(dat, t_upper = 100){
  ggplot(data = dat %>% filter(t <= t_upper)) +
  aes(x = t, y = x_pre) +
  geom_path() +
  geom_point() +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 1)) +
  ylab("x_t")
}

# 
gg_chaos <- function(dat, dat_line){
  ggplot(data = dat) +
    aes(x = x_pre, y = x_post) +
    geom_path(data = dat_line, color = "blue") +  # 
    # (step 0)
    geom_segment(data = dat %>% filter(t == 1), 
                 aes(xend = x_pre, yend = 0), alpha = 0.4, linewidth = 0.2) +
    # step 1 
    geom_segment(data = dat %>% filter(t > 1), 
                 aes(xend = x_pre, yend = x_pre), alpha = 0.4, linewidth = 0.2) +
    # 
    geom_segment(aes(xend = x_post, yend = x_post), alpha = 0.4, linewidth = 0.2, linetype = "dashed") +
    geom_point()+
    scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0, 1)) +
    scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 1)) +
    xlab("x_t") + ylab("x_t+1")
}

# 
dat %>% 
  gg_chaos(dat_line)
